FT  21 NOV 94 / What the paper says
On the economy: 'What we are saying is completely at odds with their (Tory
supporters') experience.'
On the NHS:
'The best result for the next 12 months would be zero media coverage.'
On the media:
'We need to feed our friends and potential friends in the press with good
stories.'
On voters and
the media:
'The influence of the media on voters' perceptions cannot be overstated.'
On Mr Tony Blair:
'If Blair turns out to be as good as he looks we have a problem.'
